**Phase B (HTTP check) fails:** `GET /api/live` returns 0 bytes вЂ” the client never receives response headers.

**Root cause:** `new Response(stream, { headers })` in Next.js App Router does not flush the HTTP status line and headers until the first byte of the body is written. The `ReadableStream` only enqueues data when ClickHouse returns events. When ClickHouse is unavailable (or returns empty results), nothing is enqueued and the client hangs indefinitely.

This affects both dev and production mode. The unit tests all pass because they call `GET()` in-process and inspect the `Response` object вЂ” they never exercise the HTTP serialization path.

**Fix (one line):** add `controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(":\n\n"));` at the top of the `start(controller)` callback in `src/app/api/live/route.ts:26`, before `setInterval`. SSE clients treat `:` lines as comments and discard them; this is the standard pattern for immediately flushing headers on connect.
